<br>
Are FT items really a big deal?  I mean, look at FT 1, it's 1 added mana regen per tick.  15 seconds a tick, that amounts to 5 points of added mana regen per minute.  The highest FT item I've seen in game thus far is FT 5, which is 25 added mana regen.<br>
<br>
Now, all the items with this function also happen to be amazing items (CT's brain, Shawl, Tunare earring/sword, Burrower robe thing, etc.) but would FT really factor in to getting them?  I mean, the driving desire for the Coldain shawl has gotta be FT for most people, but does it really make a difference?  I started on my shawl, but got to 5 before giving up and heading off to Giant faction (FINALLY).<br>
<br>
Now, my tailoring is back to improving, got it to 180-sumthin.  Would screwing with my faction (still no Kael gear mind you) and switch to Coldain temporarily to finish off the shawl (Got the shell from SG already) be worth it for the added 2 wisdom, and FT 1?  I wouldn't even be using this on raids, for the most part.  I generally mooch a 35+ resist shoulder off mages...<br>
<br>
Just a thought.  *shrug*  Although, another alternative is just jumping Xaviel in GD and taking his Crystal Chitin gear.  I'd never take that stuff off. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=63622">Xican's crappy profile</a>
<BR>
<i>It's better to swallow blood than pride.</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usyldane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>syldane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#333399>(2/25/02 6:40:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26252.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FT items...</span><hr size=1> Not that it makes a big difference, but a tick is six seconds, so there are 10 ticks in a minute.  FT one isn't that much by itself, but it's a cumulative thing.  The thing to do is time how long it takes you to go from zero to full mana, go to a mana calculator and get your total mana including WIS and Mana items, then divide out your mana regen per minute, then divide by 10 for your average mana regen per tick.  Seems like it works out to around 32-34 for me.  Been a while though, so I probably need to do it again.  Anyway, adding one to that number honestly doesn't give much in the way of a noticable improvement in regen rates.  Over a course of five minutes, I would receive 50 mana, not even two ticks worth of mana.  But it's enough to cast ensnare again if you are OUT of mana and cant get any distance to med a quick tick.<br>
<br>
Also consider that it regens while you are running around and NOT medding.  There you get a much better relative figure, so you may find that you won't have to med quite as much when you get to your exping location after teleporting all those people that are travel-challenged. <p><P>Syldane Dreamingwulf <BR>
Druid of Tunare<BR>
Sudden Vengeance<BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uxaviel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xaviel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#333399>(2/25/02 3:49:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26252.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/webftpspace/signature/photo.jpeg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FT items...</span><hr size=1> Compare it to stuff we already know.  Mask of the Hunter = FT3 ... is Mask of the Hunter a big deal?  PotG = FT6... can you notice a difference with and without PotG?  C3 is FT14... can you notice a difference with C3?<br>
<br>
Regarding the shawl itself... I have one, but I don't wear it.  I had a Strength of the Elements before I even started the quest.  However, I did it in anticipation of 8th, 9th, and 10th shawls which ideally would have at least FT3, which when figured into the rest, does become quite significant.  Or at the very least, it is the only way for a caster to distinguish themselves to any measureable degree with equipment, in a raid situation (and solo as well, but AC/hp help solo and small group already a bit).<br>
